eu.kidf.diversicon.cli

Class DiverCli

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.kidf.diversicon.cli.DiverCli

  • public final class DiverCli
extends Object
    Provides a Command Line Interface to Diversicon. Can be run as program or you can use of(java.lang.String...) factory method to create instances of this object. After creation, you will need to call run() method.

    All output for user is handled via Logback logging starting at info level.

    Since:
    0.1.0

      • findProjectFileOrCreateDefault

        public File findProjectFileOrCreateDefault(String filepath,
                                  String databaseId)
        Finds a configuration file in getProjectDir(). If file is not present it is created from template indicated by databaseId. If database type is unknown, use DEFAULT_DB_IDENTIFIER as databaseId.
        Parameters:
        filepath - Relative filepath with file name and extension included. i.e. abc/myfile.xml, which will be first searched in getProjectDir()/abc/myfile.xml if file is not found, it is searched in template resource folder for the specified database type and copied to current getProjectDir().
        databaseId - If unknown use DEFAULT_DB_IDENTIFIER
        Throws:
        DiverCliNotFoundException - if no file is found
        Since:
        0.1.0
        See Also:
        findProjectFile(String)
